Sub Projects
When you wish to define mods that span multiple Gradle projects (common in multi-platform setups), you can do so by specifying the source set name and the project path.


loom {
    mods {
        "example-mod" {
            sourceSet sourceSets.main
            sourceSet("main", ":core")
        }
    }
}
